        "type": "document",
        "content": "type: document\napp_id: docs\nskill_id: document\nstatus: finished\ntitle: Berlin AI Meetup Preparation Checklist\nfilename: Berlin_AI_Meetup_Checklist.docx\nword_count: 244\npage_count: 1\ndocx_model:\n  title: Berlin AI Meetup Preparation Checklist\n  filename: Berlin_AI_Meetup_Checklist.docx\n  blocks[12]:\n    - type: heading\n      level: 1\n      text: \"Practical Preparation Checklist: AI Builders Meetups\"\n    - type: paragraph\n      runs[1]{text}:\n        \"This checklist is tailored for your upcoming events on June 18 and July 3, 2026, focusing on networking with open-source builders and preparing a practical demo.\"\n    - type: heading\n      level: 2\n      text: 1. Logistics & Essentials\n    - type: list\n      ordered: false\n      items[4]: Confirm the specific Factory Berlin campus (usually Lohmühlenstraße or Görlitzer Park) for the June 18 event.,Charge your laptop and bring a power brick—meetups often involve spontaneous 'over-the-shoulder' code reviews.,Update your LinkedIn QR code or digital business card for quick sharing.,\"Check public transport: Factory Berlin is well-connected via the U1/U3 or Ringbahn (Treptower Park).\"\n    - type: heading\n      level: 2\n      text: \"2. Event-Specific Tasks: June 18 (Factory Berlin)\"\n    - type: paragraph\n      runs[1]{text,bold}:\n        \"Goal: Connect with local open-source AI builders.\",true\n    - type: list\n      ordered: false\n      items[3]: \"Prepare a 30-second 'Builder Intro': What are you currently working on? Which open-source stacks (e.g., LangChain, Ollama, PyTorch) are you using?\",\"Have 1-2 specific questions ready for the community (e.g., 'How are you handling RAG latency?' or 'What's your favorite local LLM for dev?').\",Star relevant GitHub repos you want to discuss so they are easy to find on your phone/laptop.\n    - type: heading\n      level: 2\n      text: \"3. Event-Specific Tasks: July 3 (Kreuzberg)\"\n    - type: paragraph\n      runs[1]{text,bold}:\n        \"Goal: Present a demo idea.\",true\n    - type: list\n      ordered: false\n      items[3]: \"Refine your 'Demo Idea': It doesn't need to be finished, but it should solve a clear problem.\",Prepare a 'Paper Prototype' or basic UI mockup if the code isn't ready—visuals help people give better feedback.,\"Identify your 'Ask': What do you need help with for this demo? (e.g., architecture, UI/UX, or finding a contributor).\"\n    - type: heading\n      level: 2\n      text: 4. Networking & Social Strategy\n    - type: list\n      ordered: false\n      items[3]: Aim to speak to at least 3 people you don't know.,Follow up within 24 hours on LinkedIn or via email with anyone you had a meaningful technical exchange with.,Take a photo of the whiteboard or any interesting slides (with permission) for later reference.\ndocx_s3_key: chatfiles/50c1a4b9-cad1-4ea9-bc2a-fc7c616d8293/20260610_162333_5b6ce42d_doc_538da4c5.docx.bin\nscreenshot_s3_keys:\n  \"1\": chatfiles/50c1a4b9-cad1-4ea9-bc2a-fc7c616d8293/20260610_162333_5b6ce42d_doc_538da4c5_p1.png.bin\naes_key: ONX9Mi0RjQJ/RRq6nciTwdcUrDsZ+pYiSkGtDqH5Gr8=\naes_nonce: \"\"\nvault_wrapped_aes_key: \"vault:v1:k9q/U0yfpJLEaT6t5R2byZfg7y7S1OtW3AjjpqJJont+ix5wgZX1h74h/TpR34IA5Vwje+gKbMeCxTDDSPfEWt++BogYOQuV\"",
